voices.mp3Text: Comes now the King of Bones!
The King declares this one in the bag!
Submit to the Empire of Bone.
He he ha ha! Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Your tongue makes debts my sword collects!
You come to a bad end.
A fine skin to drape o'er my bones.
What a wretched bag of skin you were.
I pitied you, with your flea-bitten pelt.
I'd not give a rotten cork for that lousy hide.
Your bones will line my garden path.
Oh you'll come back, as dice and dominoes.
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha!
I have no use for an exoskeleton!
What lacks a skeleton also lacks a soul!
A small pile of bones you'll make!
A more repugnant skeleton I've never seen!
What's this, Sand King, no bones?
Clinkz… still playing at bow'n arrows, I see.
Oh Queen of Pain, if I had flesh I would let you torment it.
Ah, Queen of Pain, my bones are yours to crack.
Don't expect me to sing your dirge.
The Death of Dirge is a most pleasant melody.
Dirge's death plays sweetly in my ears.
Dirge… learn from the master and bow to your king.
Not for the likes of you.
I'd empty the treasury for this.
By my bones, I swear revenge!
Many the day I shall rest in clay!
This bone shall stick in your throat!
Grind me to powder, even then I shall return!
I'm unfettered by the needs of the flesh.
I owe many days to the grave.
Long live the king, which is to say: Me.
Would you jump in my grave that fast?
Any pretenders to my throne will be sorely disappointed.
I've had a lovely tour of the boneyard.
The King of Bones reigns again.
You can't kill what's already dead.
Death has no grip on me!
Bone is strongest where it's mended.
Now it's your turn to die.
See you sooner than you think!
The grave won't long hold me!
Don't carve my headstone just yet.
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Tis the third reign of Skeleton King!
You just can't keep me down.

text: With 3 enemies and no allies within 400 radius
Third and more attempts within 10 seconds
Third and more attempts within 10 seconds

voices.mp3Text: The empire requires more bones. My neighbors have surrendered all of theirs. Who's next? Who's next?
I'm a robust specimen to be sure.
I've lived one life full already, and now another to repent.
From the Ivory Forest to the Towers of Ostarion, not a knuckle cracks without my knowledge.
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha!
Oh how the skeletons shall dance!
